---
// src/components/ScienceSection.astro
---

<section id="science" class="w-full bg-[var(--theme-canvas-soft)] border-t border-[var(--theme-hairline)] py-section px-4 md:px-lg">
  <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-mono text-caption-mono text-[var(--theme-body)] uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">The Engine</h2>
      <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-display-lg text-[var(--theme-ink)] tracking-[-1.28px] mb-6">Based on the Phase Response Curve</h3>
      <p class="font-sans text-[18px] text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-[1.6] max-w-[600px] mx-auto">
        Learn how to adjust your sleep schedule effectively using the biological principles of light exposure, core temperature, and melatonin timing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- SEO Content Section -->
    <div class="space-y-16 mb-20">
      
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-[24px] text-[var(--theme-ink)] tracking-tight">The Science of Circadian Rhythm Shifting</h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-relaxed text-[16px]">
          At the core of human biology is the circadian rhythm, an internal 24-hour master clock that dictates when we feel alert and when we feel sleepy. If you have ever wondered <strong>how to adjust your sleep cycle</strong> without feeling exhausted, the secret lies in understanding your Core Body Temperature Minimum (CBTmin). Your CBTmin typically occurs about two to three hours before your natural wake time. It serves as the absolute biological anchor for your internal clock.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-relaxed text-[16px]">
          The mechanism that controls this anchor is called the <strong>Phase Response Curve</strong> (PRC). The PRC maps exactly how external stimuli—primarily bright light exposure—can reset your body clock. If you seek bright light immediately <em>after</em> your CBTmin (early morning), you will phase advance your clock, shifting it earlier. Conversely, seeking light <em>before</em> your CBTmin (late evening) causes a phase delay, pushing your biological night later. Our intelligent <strong>jet lag calculator</strong> maps these exact biological windows, ensuring you never accidentally shift your clock in the wrong direction.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-[24px] text-[var(--theme-ink)] tracking-tight">Beating Jet Lag & Managing Night Shifts</h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-relaxed text-[16px]">
          Travel across multiple time zones fundamentally breaks the alignment between your internal circadian rhythm and the external environment. <strong>Overcoming jet lag fast</strong> requires a mathematical approach to light exposure. Without a planned protocol, travelers often expose themselves to bright sunshine at the exact wrong biological time, inadvertently worsening their jet lag by pushing their clock the wrong way.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-relaxed text-[16px]">
          This biological mismatch isn't limited to travel. For healthcare workers, first responders, and overnight employees figuring out <strong>how to adjust a sleep schedule to a night shift</strong>, the challenge is identical. By artificially controlling your light exposure and darkness periods using our generated timelines, you can effectively simulate time zone travel without leaving your city, helping mitigate the health impacts associated with shift work sleep disorder.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-[24px] text-[var(--theme-ink)] tracking-tight">How the Adjustment Protocol Works</h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-relaxed text-[16px]">
          When you need to know exactly <strong>how to adjust your sleep schedule</strong>, guesswork fails. Adjust Sleep functions as a precise biological scheduler. You input your normal sleep habits, departure city, and destination, and the algorithm determines the optimal daily shift—typically moving your biological clock by about 1 hour per day.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-relaxed text-[16px]">
          The protocol relies heavily on accurate <strong>melatonin timing</strong>. Melatonin acts on a mirrored Phase Response Curve to light. By taking a micro-dose of melatonin (0.5mg–3.0mg) precisely when your body expects its natural Dim Light Melatonin Onset (DLMO), you create a powerful synergy with light avoidance. This combined approach of perfectly timed light seeking, dark avoidance, and melatonin supplementation is the fastest, safest way to fully reset your body clock and arrive at your destination fully adapted.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <div class="pt-12 border-t border-[var(--theme-hairline-strong)]">
      <h3 class="font-mono text-caption-mono text-[var(--theme-body)] uppercase tracking-wider mb-8 text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
      
      <div class="space-y-6 max-w-[700px] mx-auto">
        <div class="pb-6 border-b border-[var(--theme-hairline)]">
          <h4 class="font-sans font-medium text-body-lg text-[var(--theme-ink)] mb-2">How long does it take to adjust your sleep cycle?</h4>
          <p class="text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-relaxed text-[15px]">
            The human body can naturally shift its circadian rhythm by approximately 1 hour per day. For example, a 5-hour time zone difference (like New York to London) will take a healthy adult about 5 days of strict light exposure and darkness protocols to fully adapt.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pb-6 border-b border-[var(--theme-hairline)]">
          <h4 class="font-sans font-medium text-body-lg text-[var(--theme-ink)] mb-2">Does the jet lag calculator work for shift workers?</h4>
          <p class="text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-relaxed text-[15px]">
            Yes. While built primarily for aviation, shift workers can use the tool by inputting their current city as the departure, and selecting a destination timezone that matches their required waking hours. Following the resulting light exposure plan will safely shift your circadian rhythm.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pb-6 border-b border-[var(--theme-hairline)]">
          <h4 class="font-sans font-medium text-body-lg text-[var(--theme-ink)] mb-2">Why is melatonin timing so important?</h4>
          <p class="text-[var(--theme-body)] leading-relaxed text-[15px]">
            Taking melatonin right before you sleep is actually too late to shift your body clock. For circadian adjustment, melatonin must be taken at a very specific biological window (usually earlier in the evening) to effectively trick your brain into initiating its sleep phase earlier.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
